properties.FacilityDescription:
Overview

Notrebes Bend Park is positioned on the Arkansas River, close to Merrisach Lake and the Arkansas Post Canal. The small, quaint campground is along the Mississippi Flyway, the route millions of migratory birds take to get to and from the Gulf of Mexico.

Natural Features:

Notrebes Bend sits on the main stem of the Arkansas River beside the Wilbur D. Mills Dam. Just upriver is the Arkansas Post Canal, which stretches east to connect with the White River.

Recreation:

The Wilbur D. Mills Lock and Dam attracts anglers with an abundance of largemouth bass, crappie, bream and catfish. Boating, hiking and birding are also popular pastimes.

Facilities:

Notrebes Bend offers 30 campsites with 50 amp electric hookups, drinking water and campfire rings. Twenty-four sites may be reserved.

Nearby Attractions:

The Arkansas Post National Memorial marks the spot for the first European village built west of the Mississippi River in 1686. The White River National Wildlife Refuge is also nearby, offering excellent wildlife viewing.
properties.FacilityDirections: From DeWitt Arkansas, take US-165 south for 8.1 miles. Exit onto State Route 44 east  and continue south for 5.3 miles to Tichnor. Take Tichnor Blacktop Road for 10 miles, cross the Arkansas Post Canal Bridge, and turn right onto Wilbur D. Mills Road. Continue for 6.5 miles and enter park.
